reviews.review_text: dead in the desert great memories... freezing cold everywhere else, the dead setup outside with the sun setting just as second set started..beautiful show, worth the download for Hornsby's Valley Road.jerry rips it!! thanks for the memories!!

Sound is quite good... This recording seems to sound better to me than the board (at least the vocals and most of the band stands out in this recording with way less muffled sound). S-Board?
 Highlights include a smokin' second set closing out with a real nice Wheel> Playin' In The Band Reprise> Goin' Down The Road... sweet!

Those Were The Days My Friends Cream Puff Peace is correct, this recording is better than the sound board. .......My friends and I lit out for Phoenix with only a sleeping bag and a carry on out of Ontario Airport, CA in the wake of the legendary Grateful Dead Key board player, Brent Mydland's passing with no plans of how we would get to Compton Terrace or where we would stay in between shows. .......Upon touching down at Sky Harbor, we were met by a total fox whose long brown hair was topped by a  chauffeur's cap in full uniform. She motioned toward her limo and asked if we needed a ride to the Dead show. ( I guess the tie dyes gave it away ) I told her, "yes but I don't think we can afford the ride". She just smiled said, " sure you can, there's 8 of you and that would be only $5.00 a piece". .......She even took us to a liquor store to pick up a disposable ice chest, ice and beer on the way to the show. She was only one of the great people we met that weekend while seeing one of the most amazing bands in rock and roll history.
